# Cloudflare Pages response headers for the production web build.
#
# The web SQLite engine (wa-sqlite/OPFS) talks to its worker over a
# SharedArrayBuffer, which browsers only expose to cross-origin-isolated pages.
# Isolation requires these two headers on the document — the metro.config.js
# headers only cover the dev server, so the production host must send its own.
#
# COEP is `credentialless` (not `require-corp`) so Firebase's cross-origin auth
# resources load without a CORP header while isolation is preserved; COOP stays
# `same-origin` because web sign-in uses the redirect flow, not a popup.
/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless
